This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it discusses the use of Network Functions Virtualization (NFV) to manage network functions and maintain detailed per- and cross-flow state. It may also belong to the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it discusses the need for careful management of state to ensure correctness and security. Additionally, it could be categorized under Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) as it discusses the use of an external state store and state management algorithms for efficient operation. It may also fall under the sub-categories of Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) as it discusses the need for metadata maintenance and performance optimization.
